    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>FOLLOW THE LINKS</span><b>, By Brykanst</b><br><br>If you follow the links on the page it tells you that it changes to a hammer, and the hammer changes into cleric guantlets that are dropable and give 20 Wis, and these guantlets can change back to the hammer.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>SHAPE-CHANGING ITEM?</span><b>, By Moonlore</b><br><br>Ok, so sue me, I looked in spdat.eff. There were two spells, Transmute Gauntlets and Transmute Hammer. The effect was to summon an item. My theory? If you were to click on these Gauntlets, it would &#34;consume&#34; them, and summon a Hammer that was ALSO expendable, with the effect &#34;Transmute: Gauntlets&#34;.
What does all this mean? An item that can CHANGE FORM from one type of item to another. Sweet!

<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>GOOD GOD!</span><b>, By Alonsus mindreaver</b><br><br>Look at these wicked stats!  I doubt I would have the cojones to destroy what looks to be the best caster item in the game.  That'd be like throwing your Ragebringer.  Most likely better as is, sides what is a caster gonna do with a hammer?

<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>THESE EFFECTS...</span><b>, By Aymen</b><br><br>The effect: Transmute Hammer means that the gloves will morph into some type of hammer.  The hammer will likely have uber stats as well.  The effect on the hammer will be effect: Transmute Gloves, and the hammer will be expendable.  Essentially what you have there is an item that can be changed from one to the other at will.
<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>PLEASE!</span><b>, By Feliciana</b><br><br>You guys have got to be kidding me, how many times has venril sathir been killed, on HOW many servers?  This has to be a component for an epic quest, 5lb gloves with amazing stats, and an unkown expendable effect, put it together!  It fits so neatly into the scheme of the way that they formulate these quests it's just silly, not to mention the timing of the find.   One last note, I am not sure what class venril is, (never been anywhere near him), but the poison and disease resists suggest possibly for the necro quest.<br><hr size='1'></td>
